2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper investigates the role of cooperation in managing interference in wireless networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the design and analysis of a communication system. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the transmission of data over a wireless channel. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves the use of coding schemes and mathematical analysis to optimize the performance of a communication system.
